  "text": "At present, fiber Bragg gratings with an aperiodic change in the refractive index are used [CITATION_1] . In this case, the signal reflected from the grating represents a certain spectrum. By analyzing the parameters of which, it is possible to determine the changes in the temperature and strain parameters independently of each other, while when using a periodic lattice, it is necessary to compensate for the influence of one of the parameters during signal processing. Figure 1 shows the reflection spectra of periodic and aperiodic gratings.",
